<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus j&otilde;ustub 1995. aasta 1. jaanuaril. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act enters into force on 1 January 1995. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eesti territooriumil kuni 1992. aasta 1. jaanuarini k&auml;ibele lubatud m&otilde;&otilde;tevahendid ning Riigi Standardiametilt k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumiseni t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse saanud m&otilde;&otilde;tevahendid omavad t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust selle kehtivusaja l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Measuring instruments which were approved for use in Estonia until 1 January 1992 and measuring instruments which received type approval from the National Standards Board before the entry into force of this Act have type approval until the period of validity thereof expires. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist v&auml;lja antud riiklikud tegevuslitsentsid m&otilde;&otilde;tevahendite taatlemiseks kehtivad neil m&auml;rgitud kuup&auml;evani, kuid mitte kauem kui 2001. aasta 31. detsembrini. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) State activity licences for the verification of measuring instruments which were issued before the entry into force of this Act are valid until the date specified on the licences but not for longer than until 31 December 2001. (14.06.2000 entered into force 21.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 55, 358) </inglise>
